WHO   — GCE VECTREX — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — Unique among consoles, the Vectrex came with its own built-in vector monitor — it drew crisp glowing lines directly, not a grid of pixels, so it never needed a TV. A Motorola 6809 steered the beam through a DAC, and plastic overlays added colour to the black-and-white screen.
WHERE — the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
